display_label":"Yale Class of 1849; Dwight became the eighth university president","link_text":"Timothy Dwight"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"education","header":"Captained Yale Navy's founding boat, 1845","body":"In August 1845, Lockwood captained the Augusta, an eight-oared cedar shell his classmates bought for $170, later identified as the vessel that launched what became the Yale Navy. He graduated with the class of 1849 alongside Timothy Dwight, who would become the university's eighth president."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Staffed two Union generals; built Norwalk's banking empire","body":"After serving on the staffs of Major-Generals King and Russell in the Civil War, Lockwood became president of Fairfield County National Bank and the Danbury and Norwalk Railroad, and served three terms as a Republican representative in the Connecticut General Assembly."},{"number":3,"category":"legacy","header":"SAR member; great-grandfather burned out by British","body":"A century after British forces torched Norwalk and destroyed his great-grandfather's home, Lockwood joined the Connecticut Society of the Sons of the American Revolutionary War, a membership whose meaning ran close to home. He was also made a Knight Templar and remained active in the Norwalk Club until his final years."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Patch.com — biography of Frederick Lockwood","url":"https://patch.com/connecticut/norwalk/a-famous-norwalker"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"frederick-lockwood-1825"},"I00689":{"id":"I00689","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Carrie","last_name":"Lockwood","maiden_name":"Ayres","married_names":["Lockwood"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Carrie Ayres Lockwood"},"birth":{"year":1844,"month":2,"day":1,"city":"West Troy","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descend